# 08 Vendors and Cross-Border Transfers

## Intent
Control third-party risk and legal transfer obligations for personal/health data.

## Mandatory
- Treat external services handling personal data/PHI as processors/business associates as applicable.
- Require documented contracts (DPA/BAA where needed) before production data sharing.
- For cross-border transfers, document lawful mechanism and transfer-risk controls.
- Route new integrations through a vetted gateway/pattern with policy checks.

## Operational Rules
- Maintain processor inventory with data categories, region, and purpose.
- Reassess vendors periodically for security/compliance drift.

## Release Blockers
- Production integration without contract/assessment record.
- Undocumented transfer mechanism.
